Dear Hiring Team,

I am applying for the *Software Engineer* role on Twitch's BITS team. My background centers on building consumer-facing products and backend systems that combine interactive *TypeScript/React* experiences, resilient orchestration, and production reliability. At Sperse, I built a *consumer-facing* visual workflow platform for creating, running, and monitoring agentic swarms, translated customer feedback into shipped product improvements, and used *Temporal* for durable, resumable execution while collaborating across teams. I also architected a *multi-agent* CRM platform in *Python* and *FastAPI* serving 10,000+ users, and built a *FastMCP* server exposing 160+ backend actions with monitoring and validation.

Prior to that, at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in *Java*, *Spring Boot*, *PostgreSQL*, and *Redis*, orchestrated long-running jobs with *AWS Step Functions*, and optimized *PostgreSQL* schema design to reduce latency while surfacing data through interactive *React* visualizations. That work strengthened the systems thinking, schema design, and operational discipline needed to build reliable products that stay responsive under load and deliver clear business impact.

Twitch's mission to empower live communities and its culture of community, collaboration, and problem solving align closely with how I work. I would welcome the chance to contribute to interactive experiences that help viewers support creators while keeping the platform fast, reliable, and engaging.

I have always valued community and collaboration, and I am motivated by the opportunity to contribute to Twitch's goal of empowering live communities. I would love to discuss how my experience building resilient consumer-facing systems can support this team and its mission. I can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, and I look forward to connecting.

